cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CL

The paper deals with understanding human social interactions via computational methods, which involves analyzing 3D motion capture data of body, face, and hand motions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques to predict social signals indicates that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the use of robotics to simulate social interactions suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
